				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AOE kiting. I need an explanation and some tips!<a name="22867"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 21 04 11:19 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>... so few of them because most people are too **** lazy to twist songs.
<br />

<br />
IE. Wizard / Mages / Necro's / Melee's....
<br />

<br />
Casters sit on their arses and, maybe, drop 1 nuke per mob and do /pet attack (sometimes, not always) Never really can check on the casters, and if you blame them for not doing an effort or nuking any, they blame YOU for not singing manasong so they are OOM... Lazy, lazy, lazy... sit on their butts and nuke once in a blue moon. Thats how much work a caster is to play (except Enchanters, I know they got to bust their butts at times)
<br />

<br />
And melee's? Give me a break.... hit Autoattack, and thats it... go for a cig, a fresh can of coke, watch a movie, go pick up your sister at the airport... really, how much work is it? Sure, they gotta... kick... and taunt... and and and... use a stun or a snare, maybe a backstab/flying kick if they have that... so much work... dreadful, really...
<br />

<br />
What does bards gotta do? Sure, lets be lazy too, and only do 1 song.... WRONG! ... Second manasong is gone from the Songbuff window for 4 seconds straight the casters start whining, the cleric starts pouting and the pally cries cause he needs mana for his incrediable heals.
<br />

<br />
Or *gasp* no haste? Omg, /tell Bard Haste song PLEASE!!! Argh, we are dying, haste song !!!
<br />

<br />
Or there are less than 3-4 songs in the song window... OMG that LAZY punk bard I had in my group, he couldnt even do 3 songs. I was watching his songs... OH YES I WAS... While I was sitting on my a$ contemplating on wether or not I should nuke once (it had been 10 mins since last time I nuked) or if I should reach and grab another slice of pizza... but I was WATCHING his songs, and he was SO lazy!
<br />

<br />
Everyone &quot;knows&quot; how to play a bard, and everyone can sit and watch that you do your DUTY and keep 4 songs up 24/7 without a break...
<br />

<br />
And you all know what I'm talking about... Some clown in your group who has a lvl 11 bard and knows EVERYTHING about how bard songs are and what songs YOU should be playing to be most efficient for the group.
<br />

<br />
Please... 
<br />

<br />
when you got a bard to lvl 65;
<br />

<br />
when you mastered mezzing 4 mobs at once in tight rooms/hallways where targetting is a pain up the rear end; 
<br />

<br />
when you master the knowledge on how all songs work, what stats/effects they boost and how all those &quot;useless&quot; bard songs work, and when to use them;
<br />

<br />
when you can chainpull smoothly for 5 hours straight without one foul-up;
<br />

<br />
when you master the art of chant/charm/swarm/aoe kiting;
<br />

<br />
when you have been doing nothing but pressing 11, 22 ,33 ,44 for 100-150+ days /played in exp groups and soloing;
<br />

<br />
when you've had to see a doctor 3+ times for a sore wrist after twisting songs;
<br />

<br />
when you develop carperal vision from staring at your &quot;Cast Time bar&quot; while twisting songs over and over;
<br />

<br />
when you have learned how to deal with the constant whining from casters like YOU and melee's like YOUR FRIEND because they dont see the song/s they like in the buffwindow every freaking second they peek at it;
<br />

<br />
THEN you can come tell me how to bloody play a bard :mad:
<br />

<br />
And why there are so few of us bards? Cause unlike other classes, bards take an effort and devotion to learn and play right.
<br />

<br />
I wanna see some lvl 65 ebay bard go ahead and pull Hard adventures, or even normal ones for that matter, without screwing things up quickly.
<br />

<br />
That said, I have a grand example...
<br />

<br />
My friend /tells me &quot;What does Niv's Harmonic do?&quot;
<br />

<br />
I tell him, &quot;its an AC buff song. Around 15-30 AC buff, cant remember exactly. Why you ask?&quot;
<br />

<br />
&quot;Cause its the only song our Bard is playing&quot;
<br />

<br />
I ponder a second... &quot;What are you guys camping?&quot;
<br />

<br />
&quot;we're at the RC in PoV&quot;
<br />

<br />
I laughed... wtf? Niv's Harmonic.... yeah, bard melee + 20'ish AC is gonna make SUCH a difference vs. golems that hit for 4xx-5xx doubles.
<br />

<br />
Either a lazy bard... an ebayed bard... or just a clueless bard...
<br />

<br />
Anyhow... too much typing... time to eat pizza... wahoooo !!!</span></td>
